article.headline: TCU 53, Tulane 51
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Kevin Langford hit the game-winning shot on a turnaround jumper with 0.4 seconds remaining to give TCU a 53-51 win over Tulane on Saturday. The Horned Frogs (6-3) led by 11 points with 16 minutes remaining, but Tulane closed the gap with a 10-0 run over the next three minutes to bring the game to within a point. Tulane's Daniel Puckett tied the game at 51 with 23 seconds remaining, but Neil P. Dougherty passed to Langford for the winning basket. Brent Hackett scored 15 points for TCU, and Keion Mitchem came off the bench to add 13. Langford scored 8 points and grabbed eight rebounds. David Gomez led the Green Wave (5-4) with 31 points and nine rebounds. Puckett, Tulane's next highest scorer, had seven points and nine rebounds.
